The shortest such segment $\overline{PQ}$ will be an internal common tangent of the two cirlces, and $\angle BQD = \angle APD = 90^\circ.$  Extend $\overline{BQ}$ past $Q$ to $R$ so that $QR = PA.$  Then $APQR$ is a rectangle.

We have that $BR = BQ + QR = BQ + PA = 9 + 6 = 15$ and $AB = 25.$  Then by Pythagoras on right triangle $ARB,$
\[AR = \sqrt{AB^2 - BR^2} = \sqrt{25^2 - 15^2} = 20.\]Therefore, $PQ = AR = \boxed{20}.$

question:
For $x \ge 1,$ let $f$ be the function defined as follows:
\[f(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
\lfloor x \rfloor \left| x - \lfloor x \rfloor - \dfrac{1}{2 \lfloor x \rfloor} \right| & \text{if $x < \lfloor x \rfloor + \dfrac{1}{\lfloor x \rfloor}$}, \\
f \left( x - \dfrac{1}{\lfloor x \rfloor} \right) & \text{otherwise}.
\end{array}
\right.\]Let $g(x) = 2^{x - 2007}.$ Compute the number of points in which the graphs of $f$ and $g$ intersect.

extra.solution:
Let $n$ be an integer, and let $n \le x < n + \frac{1}{n}.$  Then
