label("$B$",B,SE);
label("$C$",C,NE);
label("$D$",D,NW);
label("$E$",I,W);
label("$F$",F,E);
[/asy]

extra.solution:
Since $\angle BAD = 60^{\circ}$, isosceles $\triangle
BAD$ is also equilateral. As a consequence, $\triangle AEB$, $\triangle AED$, $\triangle BED$, $\triangle BFD$, $\triangle
BFC$, and $\triangle CFD$ are congruent. These six triangles have equal areas and their union forms  rhombus $ABCD$, so each has area $24/6 = 4$. Rhombus $BFDE$ is the union of  $\triangle BED$ and $\triangle BFD$, so its area is $\boxed{8}.$

[asy]
pair A,B,C,D,I,F;
A=(0,0);
B=(10,0);
C=(15,8.7);
D=(5,8.7);
I=(5,2.88);
F=(10,5.82);
draw(A--B--C--D--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
draw(D--I--B--F--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
label("$A$",A,SW);
label("$B$",B,SE);
label("$C$",C,NE);
label("$D$",D,NW);
label("$E$",I,NW);
label("$F$",F,E);
draw(A--I,linewidth(0.7));
draw(F--C,linewidth(0.7));
draw(D--B,linewidth(0.7));
[/asy]

