draw(rightanglemark(O,D,P,2));
draw(Circle(O,1));
label("$O$",O,SE);
label("$P$",P,SW);
//label("$A$",A,SE);
label("$D$",D,N);
[/asy]

Triangle $POD$ is a 30-60-90 triangle, so $DO = \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}$ and $DP = \frac12$.  Therefore, the coordinates of $P$ are $\left(-\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}, -\frac12\right)$, so we have that $\cos(-150^\circ) = \cos 210^\circ = \boxed{-\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}}$.

